Importing Authorized AP Lists

 

You can import a list of authorized access points using a CSV file. Use the following values as a reference when you create the CSV file.

Field

Values

Security

 • 0 — Open

 • 1 — WEP

 • 2 — WPA-Personal

 • 3 — WPA-Enterprise

 • 4 — WPA2-Personal

 • 5 — WPA2-Enterprise

Network Mode

 • 0 — B Only

 • 1 — G Only

 • 2 — N Only

 • 3 — BG-Mixed

 • 4 — GN-Mixed

 • 5 — BGN-Mixed

Channel

 • 0 — Auto

 • 1 — 2.412

 • 2 — 2.417

 • 3 — 2.422

 • 4 — 2.427

 • 5 — 2.432

 • 6 — 2.437

 • 7 — 2.442

 • 8 — 2.447

 • 9 — 2.452

 • 10 — 2.457

 • 11 — 2.462

Encryption

 • 2 — TKIP

 • 4 — CCMP

Authentication

 • 2 — PSK

 • 1 — RADIUS

Ensure that the content in the CSV file is arranged as shown in the following example:

BSSID

Security

Encryption

Authentication

Auth_Guest

To import a list of authorized APs:

 1. Click Merge to add the list of access points that you want to import, to the access points displayed in Authorized AP Table. Click Replace to replace the APs in the table with the APs in the list that you want to import.

 2. Click Browse to locate the file that you want to import.

 3. Click Save.
